{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78cad0e1-2190-459a-ba10-f68206e4453d","content":"Since you already have `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` referenced, just run:\n\n```\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in **watch mode**. It will:\n\n1. **Run all tests** initially\n2. **Watch for file changes** — when you save edits to your test or source files, it automatically **re-runs affected tests** without a full rebuild\n\nThis is faster than `dotnet watch test` because it uses hot reload to apply changes in-process rather than restarting the entire test host.\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Run `dotnet test --hotreload` in one terminal\n2. Open `EmailValidatorTests.cs` in your editor\n3. Fix a failing test, save → tests re-run automatically\n4. Repeat until green ✅\n\nPress `Ctrl+C` to stop the session when you're done.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"eb6c7e85-f944-472c-974f-f2064e1534e5","outputTokens":205},"id":"009d7621-0efc-4790-83b6-69ea1d31b8d1","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:39:48.637Z","parentId":"00941c79-6e5e-4c55-9148-30bfc8f0c77d"}
